General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Community Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

Why should I play this class?

Slayer is a warrior class that can output high amounts of front loaded damage in a short time. That means you can enter the identity state, called Burst Mode, and instantly start dishing out her entire kit.

Her strongest skills are heavy singular hitters, which players often treat as a feedback to their character’s development.

She’s a melee back attacker and her builds improve on that. That being said, she has great maneuverability tools, on top of having maximum movement speed, which eases the frequent struggle of chasing enemies' rears.

Branding her as a melee also doesn’t tell the whole story, since she has insane range compared to the other melee options.

Being from the warrior class also means her defense and HP are on the higher end, so you shouldn’t be too afraid of taking huge chunks of damage.

TLDR: If you like big numbers and bigger boobs swords, this is the class for you.

How does my identity work?

Similar to Berserker, Slayer has a Fury meter that is filled by hitting the enemy with any one of her attacks, and can be activated once full to enter Burst Mode.

While in Burst Mode, you are provided with the following effects:

  • 20% Attack and Movement Speed and 30% Crit Rate increase.
  • Burst mode cannot be canceled.
  • You also gain access to Slayer’s greatest Skill, Bloodlust (Default keybind Z) which deals significant damage and has additionally Push Immunity, Weak Point, and Stagger.
  • After Burst Mode ends, a non-removable exhaustion debuff prevents you from gaining meter from attacks for 30 seconds.

The two class engravings available for Slayer change how her identity works.

Predator

👉 Hitting an enemy increases the identity (Fury) meter by 10% and restores 3% max Mana (1s internal cooldown).

👉 During Burst mode, increases Crit Damage by 40% but disables the Bloodlust Skill (Z).

👉 Every 3 seconds gain an exhaustion stack that increases Burst meter consumption by 10% (1s internal cooldown).

👉 When Burst mode ends, exhaustion duration is reduced by 1 second for each Fatigue stack obtained, starting at a base of 30 seconds.

👉 When exhaustion ends, the identity (Fury) meter is automatically fully refilled.

Punisher

👉 During Burst Mode, all damage +25% and Bloodlust (Z) crit rate +20%.

👉 Identity (Fury) Meter gain -25%.

👉 Burst Mode duration -50%.

👉 When Burst Mode ends, exhaustion is not applied.

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight while Burst synergies are much more infrequent.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

PREDATOR

Written by ivxn

Playstyle

Predator is a fast, back attacker, constant damage dealer, similar to the likes of Taijutsu Scrapper and Hunger Reaper.

The playstyle is based on trying to maintain the Burst Mode as long as possible, because it will run out eventually. The longer you can maintain the mode up, the faster it will start running out and when it does, you’ll enter exhaustion mode.

In exhaustion mode, you lose all of the buffs from Burst mode state (20% Move/Attack Speed, 30% Crit Rate, 40% Crit Damage and mana regeneration)

The duration of exhaustion mode is inversely proportional to the time you spent in Burst mode. That is, the longer the burst mode, the shorter the exhaustion mode.

Realistically, you will be playing at around 10 (30 seconds Burst mode, 20 seconds exhaustion) to 20 (60 seconds Burst mode, 10 seconds exhaustion) exhaustion stacks most of the time. Less than that will feel really bad. More than that you’re getting close to Trixion level.

Stat Allocation

You’ll need cooldown reduction and attack speed to maintain the Burst Mode. Crit gains more value from the +40% crit damage from the engraving.

FAQ: PREDATOR

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Is Predator viable?

It is actually a build with very high damage output, but has some flaws that can make it a bit stressful to pilot.

The exhaustion mode punishes you for not attacking during Burst Mode, and raids have been designed to have you stop attacking to pass some mechanic or gimmick. And it’s not like Adrenaline that you can keep spamming one skill, you need to actually hit something.

Brelshaza banishment will probably be the thing you’re most scared of.

There are also cutscenes (Vykas typing, Kakul-Saydon Showtime) that don’t stop time so if you’re in Burst Mode you can’t hit the boss and your meter is getting drained without you being able to maintain it. Sometimes you gotta keep in mind that waiting a bit to reactivate Burst Mode might be the best call.

Also, if you’re in a raid with players way above minimum item level, the boss will jump from one mechanic to the other, making you feel like you can never enjoy your Burst mode.

That being said, the class is completely viable and fun. It just might not be the thing for everyone.

How does it compare to other classes?

For a full swiftness class, her skills hit HARD. If you like fast and spammy gameplay, but also want to see some big numbers, this is a build for you.

In a scenario that allows you to maintain DPS, you can achieve most damage done without much effort.

Am I supposed to have mana issues?

Yes. Pray for a good support, or use mana food… Or both.

PUNISHER

Written by ivxn

Playstyle

This is your traditional fill gauge > activate fun mode > dump all skills loop gameplay.

Similar to the likes of Igniter Sorceress and Barrage Artillerist.

The faster you can return to Burst Mode and the more skills you can fit inside it the more overall damage you will deal.

Stat Allocation

Specialization will give you damage and meter generation.

Swiftness on the necklace will make you hit the limit on attack speed and movement speed, enabling Raid Captain.

* Spec/Swift also works for the bracelets, especially if you don’t have a necklace with high Swiftness.

Your amount of Swiftness becomes an important factor for being able to use  Guillotine two times in one Burst Mode.

If you want to minmax, you need 582/466 Swiftness to hit attack speed and movement speed limit with Yearning lvl 2/3.

If you have plans of doing double  Guillotine, you need around 500 Swiftness (more is even better) and a level 9  cooldown gem.

Builds

Use these builds as an example of a goal build for yourself. Using knowledge you learned from earlier in the guide make changes and adjustments to the build to your liking and enjoy the end game.

For Inferno builds checkout Hell Academy.

1.5 Cycle

The goal of this build is to fit as many skills inside your Burst as possible while keeping the rotation very synchronized.

The 1.5 number means you need one cycle and a half of your meter generation skills to fill up the identity meter.

It has very flexible Specialization breakpoints since you will be bottlenecked by the cooldown of your damage skills, which means most of the time you’ll end up filling your meter before (Brutal Impact) comes off cooldown.

And the point is to wait for it, to keep it synced.

1.0 Cycle

The goal of this build is to rotate Burst Mode as fast as possible, which means activating it as soon as it is filled.

It plays around the fact that the cooldown of Bloodlust (Z) gets reset every time you enter Burst Mode.

The 1.0 number means you need to cycle your meter generation skills only once to fill up the identity meter.

FAQ: PUNISHER

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Which build is better? Which should I choose?

They have strengths and weaknesses.

Cons

Comfortable meter generation

Room for error outside of Burst Mode, by just using Furious Claw as a filler meter generator.

Your stress will come from Burst Mode

By missing skills or boss canceling them,

or running out of time without using all skills

Flexible specialization requirements

You don’t have time to reposition during Burst Mode

Synced rotation during Burst Mode

Can’t go from 0 meter to full fast

This means you won’t benefit from unexpected damage windows if your meter is empty, cause you’ll need to wait for Spinning Sword cooldown

Two charges of Wild Rush for movement

Short damage windows aren’t your friends

You need the entirety of your Burst Mode duration to dish out full damage

Your Burst Mode is very comfortable

You have a lot of wiggle room to walk to back attacks, do minor mechanics

You get heavily punished if something goes wrong outside Burst Mode

You don’t have a second plan so you just gotta wait for skills to come back up to use them again.

You don’t run out of time for meter gen

Your goal is to fill up meter as soon as possible

BUT If you need you can delay skills to dodge something

It’s best to delay them than miss them

Needs ALL wealth runes, all meter gen tripods and high Specialization (1781+).

There’s no short cooldown/spammable skill so you gotta manage your stacks more carefully to maintain them.

Fastest 0→100% meter fill up time

I still have no idea what to do

If you want to be serious about this class, you will want to be able to play both 1.0 and 1.5, since they have strengths and weaknesses that get exposed in different scenarios. 6 Seconds is an extra, but still nice to have.

With experience, you’ll feel which is best where. You can have all skill sets ready all the time since they share the same gems, granted you’re not picking any variants.

First and foremost: start farming towards the Wealth rune from Sea Bounties if you haven’t.

For stats, as a rule of thumb, you should aim for at least 1781 Specialization with as much Swiftness as possible. This will enable you to play 1.0 and 1.5 cycles and also use two Guillotines inside one Burst Mode (reminder you also need a level 9 cooldown gem for that).

You can play 1.5 while you work towards tripod levels. Or, if you’re impatient you can buy amulets from the Auction House.

You can also “skip” one tripod level by aiming for 1808 Spec and using Punishing Draw instead of Cruel Pierce.
